title: 6.4 quake hits central alaska
author: Seattle Times Staffseattle Times News Services
text: FAIRBANKS - A strong earthquake shook central Alaska last night, but there were no reports of injuries or major damage.    The magnitude 6.4 quake struck at 9:23 p.m. and was centered about 40 miles northwest of Fairbanks. It was felt more than 300 miles away.
